title.narrative: Support to humanitarian agencies preparing for Internally Displaced Persons in Mosul region

description.narrative: This activity (Support to humanitarian agencies preparing for Internally Displaced Persons in Mosul region) is a component of Support to emergency in Iraq reported by FCDO, with a funding type of 'Multilateral organisation' and a budget of £38,135,887. This component benefits Iraq, and works in the following sector(s): Relief co-ordination and support services. , with the following implementing partners: CANADEM, Crown Agents Limited, Danish Refugee Council, International Organization for Migration (IOM), Norwegian Refugee Council, Palladium International Ltd (UK), RedR, United Nations Children's Fund (UNICEF), United Nations Office for Project Services (UNOPS). The start date is 05-09-2016 and the end date is 31-03-2019.
